To update the header in the source files:

  1. Edit the header.txt file in the maintenance directory.

  2. Go to the top level nox source directory:
     $> cd Trilinos/packages/nox

  3. run the shell script:
     $> maintenance/update_nox_headers.sh

Old way to use autoheader:

cd nox
make distclean
find . -type f \
    -not -path \*CVS\* \
    -not -path \*doc/html\* \
    -not -path \*doc/latex\* \
    -not -path \*deps\* \
    -not -path \*config\* \
    -not -path \*maintenance\* \
    -not -path \*autom4te\* \
    -not -path \*doc/includes\* \
    -not -path \*src-loca/doc\* \
    -not -name \*~ \
    -not -name .cvsignore \
    -not -name \*.o \
    -not -name \*stamp-h\* \
    -not -name \*.m4 \
    -not -name \*# \
    -not -name NOX_Config\* \
    -not -name Doxyfile\* \
    -not -name bootstrap \
    -not -name configure \
    -not -name \*.tar.gz \
    -not -name \*.a \
    -not -name LICENSE \
    -not -name .\* \
    -not -name \*.gif \
    -not -name nox.tag \
    -exec maintenance/autoheader {} maintenance/header.txt \;
